1
00:00:00,709 --> 00:00:02,961
♪

2
00:00:02,961 --> 00:00:04,796
Get ready for a
cool new card game

3
00:00:04,796 --> 00:00:07,216
that connects to a
parallel universe.

4
00:00:07,216 --> 00:00:09,134
Special cards act as portals

5
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:10,511
bringing monsters to Earth

6
00:00:10,511 --> 00:00:12,387
to become buddies with humans,

7
00:00:12,387 --> 00:00:13,847
And through
friendship and courage

8
00:00:13,847 --> 00:00:16,099
help them take on
fight challenges.

9
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:18,727
It's called Buddyfight.

10
00:00:19,645 --> 00:00:21,146
What's the matter, Gao?

11
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:22,731
Are you okay?

12
00:00:22,731 --> 00:00:24,525
Have you seen Rouga?

13
00:00:24,525 --> 00:00:28,737
Um, actually he's
left school for good.

14
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:30,656
Why don't you become his friend

15
00:00:30,656 --> 00:00:32,491
and try explaining it to him?

16
00:00:32,491 --> 00:00:33,867
You're right.

17
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:35,994
But it's too late for that now.

18
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,538
Nothing is ever too late,

19
00:00:37,538 --> 00:00:39,206
believe me.

20
00:00:39,206 --> 00:00:41,542
When you get to
be as old as I am

21
00:00:41,542 --> 00:00:42,960
you learn it's our mistakes

22
00:00:42,960 --> 00:00:44,878
that shape us into who we are.

23
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,421
I guess.

24
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,839
Then for me,

25
00:00:47,839 --> 00:00:49,049
this has taught me to try

26
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:51,051
and become friends
with everyone.

27
00:00:51,051 --> 00:02:18,639
♪

28
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:25,937
Welcome to Earth, Sir.

29
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,023
Are you interested in
doing some sightseeing?

30
00:02:28,023 --> 00:02:28,940
Sightseeing?

31
00:02:28,940 --> 00:02:30,442
What do you take me for?

32
00:02:30,442 --> 00:02:31,777
I don't have time to engage

33
00:02:31,777 --> 00:02:34,029
in such trivial nonsense.

34
00:02:34,029 --> 00:02:36,615
A knight's intellect
seeks nobler pursuits.

35
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:37,866
Sorry.

36
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,618
There's certainly
many other things to do

37
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:41,620
during your stay.

38
00:02:41,620 --> 00:02:43,622
(panting)

39
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:44,706
(barks)

40
00:02:44,706 --> 00:02:46,291
But I want popcorn!

41
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:49,294
Okay, but leave them for dinner.

42
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:50,003
Wait!

43
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:52,005
Heel, (indistinct)

44
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,716
The real reason I came
to this world is...

45
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,551
I'll just check off sightseeing.

46
00:02:58,345 --> 00:03:02,140
Deck building to victory!

47
00:03:02,140 --> 00:03:03,850
A‐B‐C.

48
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,602
Aibo Buddy Cup?

49
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:08,146
Is it that time of year again?

50
00:03:08,146 --> 00:03:11,274
What exactly is the
Aibo Buddy Cup anyway?

51
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:12,818
You really don't know?

52
00:03:12,818 --> 00:03:13,944
How could he?

53
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:14,986
Don't forget, Baku.

54
00:03:14,986 --> 00:03:16,154
He wasn't even Buddyfighting

55
00:03:16,154 --> 00:03:17,614
the last time that it was held.

56
00:03:17,614 --> 00:03:20,200
Yeah, but I figured he
would have at least heard of it.

57
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,952
The Aibo Buddy Cup,

58
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,830
also known as the
ABC Cup for short,

59
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:26,373
is a major Buddyfight tournament

60
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:27,624
open to both the elementary

61
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:30,335
and middle school
students at our school.

62
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:33,672
It's the number one event for
those in the Buddyfight class.

63
00:03:33,672 --> 00:03:36,049
And my favorite
tournament of the year.

64
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,843
Wow, sign me up!

65
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:39,177
I can hardly wait.

66
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:40,554
Before you get too excited,

67
00:03:40,554 --> 00:03:42,264
this is a team competition.

68
00:03:42,264 --> 00:03:45,016
So you'll need to form a
group of two or more students.

69
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:46,935
Huh, a team?

70
00:03:46,935 --> 00:03:47,853
Baku!

71
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:50,188
I want you to build my deck.

72
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:52,315
Sure, but only if you
listen to me, okay?

73
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:53,733
First time for everything.

74
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:55,402
You're gonna need
an analyst, too.

75
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:56,278
Am I right?

76
00:03:56,278 --> 00:03:58,613
What's an analyst?

77
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,073
Something you can eat?

78
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:03,326
An analyst is a person who
keeps track of all the card data

79
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:04,703
and recommends play strategies.

80
00:04:04,703 --> 00:04:05,954
In other words,

81
00:04:05,954 --> 00:04:08,707
she's a walking,
talking card dictionary.

82
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:09,666
Wicked!

83
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:11,042
We can use that!

84
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:12,669
So now we have a team.

85
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:15,547
All that's left to do is
come up with a good name.

86
00:04:15,547 --> 00:04:17,382
Huh?

87
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:19,259
Let's call it

88
00:04:19,259 --> 00:04:20,802
Rising Tiger.

89
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:23,889
I think that oughtta catch
their attention, hey, guys?

90
00:04:23,889 --> 00:04:26,558
You sure you want
us on your team?

91
00:04:26,558 --> 00:04:27,893
It's just that

92
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,811
we won't be much help.

93
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:32,105
Yeah, we're not strong
fighters like you are.

94
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:34,316
We don't even know
how to build a deck.

95
00:04:34,316 --> 00:04:35,817
Hey, not a problem.

96
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:37,569
You just need to
make up the numbers,

97
00:04:37,569 --> 00:04:39,237
the rest I'll do myself.

98
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,782
You think you even stand
a chance after yesterday?

99
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:44,910
Yeah, I mean, that Gao
Mikado guy destroyed Rouga

100
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,244
in just one turn.

101
00:04:46,244 --> 00:04:47,913
He obviously just got lucky.

102
00:04:47,913 --> 00:04:49,289
Beating someone
on your first turn

103
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:51,041
isn't something you can plan.

104
00:04:51,041 --> 00:04:54,044
That guy just fluked
out is all, trust me.

105
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:57,088
I think our team name should
be the Mighty Sun Fighters.

106
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,340
Huh?

107
00:04:58,340 --> 00:05:00,133
I'm already the
Mighty Sun Fighter.

108
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,843
You'll be the
Mighty Deck Builder

109
00:05:01,843 --> 00:05:03,470
and you, the Mighty Analyst.

110
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,139
So together we'd be called
the Mighty Sun Fighters.

111
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:07,182
It's a no brainer.

112
00:05:07,182 --> 00:05:08,767
Super cool, don't you think?

113
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,602
Sounds to me like you just
wanna take all the credit.

114
00:05:10,602 --> 00:05:11,812
No way, Jose.

115
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:14,105
But I will be the
only one fighting.

116
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:16,399
Let's keep brainstorming, guys.

117
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,735
The Mighty Sun Fighters
is a stupid name.

118
00:05:18,735 --> 00:05:20,028
Fine, who needs ya?

119
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:20,987
I'll build my own deck!

120
00:05:20,987 --> 00:05:22,239
How hard can it be

121
00:05:22,239 --> 00:05:23,907
to slap a few cards
together anyway?

122
00:05:23,907 --> 00:05:25,283
Oh, yeah, you think so?

123
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:26,952
In that case I'll never ever

124
00:05:26,952 --> 00:05:28,954
build a deck for you again.

125
00:05:28,954 --> 00:05:30,580
And I'll form my own team.

126
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,791
Good luck with that.

127
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,459
Come on, boys.

128
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:36,586
♪

129
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,547
And now to finish them off.

130
00:05:38,547 --> 00:05:41,299
Hey, Geronimo, go
and attack the fighter.

131
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:43,009
Not bad at all.

132
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:44,636
For a Dragon Knight deck

133
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:46,847
it seems fairly
well put together.

134
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:48,849
(screaming)

135
00:05:48,849 --> 00:05:49,933
Game over.

136
00:05:49,933 --> 00:05:52,143
Winner, Noboru Kodo.

137
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:54,396
Buddy Cup here I come.

138
00:05:54,396 --> 00:05:55,438
Like I told you,

139
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:57,274
you're just too strong for me.

140
00:05:57,274 --> 00:05:59,568
Come on, you're up Nitani.

141
00:05:59,568 --> 00:06:01,862
Uh, yeah.

142
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,321
What's with him?

143
00:06:03,321 --> 00:06:05,156
‐Raise the flag.
‐Raise the flag.

144
00:06:05,156 --> 00:06:07,367
I fight for Dragon World.

145
00:06:07,367 --> 00:06:09,286
I sense trouble in his future.

146
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,956
Why do you have
to fight about it?

147
00:06:12,956 --> 00:06:16,042
You are gonna regret
running away like this, Baku.

148
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,505
I'm okay.

149
00:06:20,505 --> 00:06:21,923
See?

150
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:23,633
You're already
regretting it, aren't you?

151
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:24,885
No, not at all.

152
00:06:24,885 --> 00:06:28,471
I think I just need
something to eat.

153
00:06:28,471 --> 00:06:29,347
Here you go.

154
00:06:29,347 --> 00:06:30,932
It's high in potassium.

155
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:32,517
Huh?

156
00:06:32,517 --> 00:06:34,185
Hurry up and eat it, young man,

157
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:36,354
before it spoils.

158
00:06:36,354 --> 00:06:39,691
Okay, don't mind if I do.

159
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,027
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

160
00:06:42,027 --> 00:06:44,029
That did the trick.

161
00:06:44,029 --> 00:06:45,822
As a thanks for this banana I,

162
00:06:45,822 --> 00:06:47,574
the grand master
of all deck builders,

163
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,743
will build your deck.

164
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:52,078
You really mean it?

165
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:55,498
This deck building
stuff is easy.

166
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:56,666
Hey.

167
00:06:56,666 --> 00:06:59,836
This guy here is one
of my favorite monsters.

168
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:02,172
Yeah, I'm gonna
need this one here,

169
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:05,091
and this one too
to increase my gauge.

170
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:08,053
There, my most powerful one yet.

171
00:07:08,053 --> 00:07:11,556
You sure they're all gonna
fit into your deck case?

172
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:13,266
Nope, not even close.

173
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:14,225
Didn't think so.

174
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,353
Maybe if I push a little harder.

175
00:07:16,353 --> 00:07:18,063
(ringing)

176
00:07:19,230 --> 00:07:20,565
Kuguru?

177
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:23,818
She said her house
was supposed to be

178
00:07:23,818 --> 00:07:25,403
around here somewhere, right?

179
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,822
Uh, you mean like that big
one right in front of us?

180
00:07:27,822 --> 00:07:30,033
Oh, yeah.

181
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,076
Man.

182
00:07:31,076 --> 00:07:33,578
Don't tell me she lives here.

183
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,122
What's this?

184
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:36,915
Ah!

185
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:37,707
Hi, guys.

186
00:07:37,707 --> 00:07:39,376
Find the place okay?

187
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:43,004
Yeah, but what did you want
us to disguise ourselves for?

188
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:44,798
Please, make yourself at home.

189
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:47,842
Man, this place is huge.

190
00:07:47,842 --> 00:07:49,761
Hey, those are Baku's shoes.

191
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:52,097
And that's why you're incognito.

192
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:54,683
So Tetsuya.

193
00:07:54,683 --> 00:07:56,810
What's the
objective of your deck?

194
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:57,894
That's easy.

195
00:07:57,894 --> 00:07:59,562
It's to win, of course, yo.

196
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:01,773
Yeah, but how do
you plan to win?

197
00:08:01,773 --> 00:08:02,774
A speedy attack

198
00:08:02,774 --> 00:08:04,275
or defend and then a counter

199
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:06,820
or maybe a deadly combo deck?

200
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,446
It all sounds good.

201
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:10,407
How about just giving
me a little of each.

202
00:08:10,407 --> 00:08:11,950
Come on, you can't
have everything.

203
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:14,119
That would be like
asking a pro sumo wrestler

204
00:08:14,119 --> 00:08:16,287
to be a gymnast.

205
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:20,458
Nothing's impossible
for Demon Lord Asmodai.

206
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:24,379
Sumo gymnast!

207
00:08:24,379 --> 00:08:25,255
Boo‐yah.

208
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:26,464
He went there.

209
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:29,551
Anyway, you really need
to start with a focus.

210
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:31,970
Or maybe a specific
card you wanna use.

211
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:35,473
Hm.

212
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,266
Sure!

213
00:08:36,266 --> 00:08:37,767
I pick Asmodai.

214
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,018
Huh?

215
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:40,895
How about a deck with
a bunch of Asmodais

216
00:08:40,895 --> 00:08:43,148
to show off their
wicked skills, yo.

217
00:08:43,148 --> 00:08:44,315
Tetsuya.

218
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:46,026
Oh yeah, and then we
could call it something

219
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:49,154
like Asmodai's Crazy
Dance Spectacular Deck.

220
00:08:49,154 --> 00:08:51,948
Actually, I'd prefer
something a little edgier.

221
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,742
Not a problem.

222
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:54,993
I can work with that.

223
00:08:54,993 --> 00:08:56,494
Yeah, sounds good.

224
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:58,163
What are we doing here again?

225
00:08:58,163 --> 00:09:00,290
I don't know.

226
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:03,001
First we'll add more Asmodais.

227
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:05,420
Give me Asmodai's
trends and abilities.

228
00:09:05,420 --> 00:09:06,504
You got it.

229
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:07,964
And his synergy.

230
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:08,715
Wow, yo.

231
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:10,842
He's racing.

232
00:09:10,842 --> 00:09:12,969
So that's a deck
builder at work.

233
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:14,721
Amazing.

234
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:16,806
♪

235
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:17,682
Game over.

236
00:09:17,682 --> 00:09:20,268
Winner, Naboru Kodo.

237
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,520
That's ten wins in a row!

238
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,814
You're just too
strong for us, Naboru.

239
00:09:24,814 --> 00:09:26,941
Okay, let's go again, Maihama.

240
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:27,984
But I can't.

241
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:30,528
I've got chess club, remember?

242
00:09:30,528 --> 00:09:32,530
Yeah, and I've got
a test to study for.

243
00:09:32,530 --> 00:09:33,364
All right.

244
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:35,200
Catch you later, then.

245
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:37,243
Kid ain't bad.

246
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:42,207
♪

247
00:09:42,207 --> 00:09:45,543
You could be a
better Buddyfighter.

248
00:09:45,543 --> 00:09:47,170
Slow down, kid.

249
00:09:47,170 --> 00:09:48,713
Hey, kid.

250
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:50,965
Hey, listen.

251
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:51,966
Hey.

252
00:09:51,966 --> 00:09:53,301
I watched your fight back there

253
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:55,929
and I think I can help.

254
00:09:55,929 --> 00:09:57,639
Your deck's well balanced.

255
00:09:57,639 --> 00:09:59,641
But you let your
gauge get too low.

256
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:02,560
Against a good
fighter it will cost you.

257
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:04,646
Are you listening?

258
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:07,565
Why do you keep following me?

259
00:10:07,565 --> 00:10:09,943
Why don't you add an
El Quixote to your deck?

260
00:10:09,943 --> 00:10:13,905
It has a handy ability
to increase your gauge.

261
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:16,533
I don't actually like
the El Quixote card.

262
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:17,408
Huh?

263
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:18,868
What are you talking about?

264
00:10:20,078 --> 00:10:20,829
Okay.

265
00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:22,914
That should do it.

266
00:10:22,914 --> 00:10:24,249
Wow.

267
00:10:24,249 --> 00:10:25,750
You'll get stronger
using your deck

268
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,085
with every match you play.

269
00:10:27,085 --> 00:10:29,504
This is so totally wicked.

270
00:10:29,504 --> 00:10:33,550
There's no way I could
have built a deck like this.

271
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,260
Let's blow this place, Drum.

272
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:36,845
Huh, why?

273
00:10:36,845 --> 00:10:38,388
Hey, wait!

274
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:39,097
Look, Kugaru.

275
