546
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:07,748
At least I still have
a Dragonic Thunder.

547
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:08,708
Huh?

548
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,626
Guard against it, Naboru.

549
00:20:10,626 --> 00:20:12,253
Use your Dragonic Thunder.

550
00:20:12,253 --> 00:20:15,673
He can't even if he wanted to.

551
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:17,883
If I just had one more gauge.

552
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:21,637
Two Platoon Drop Kick!

553
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:23,931
After that double Asmodai attack

554
00:20:23,931 --> 00:20:26,016
he's got three life points left.

555
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:27,935
Begin final phase.

556
00:20:27,935 --> 00:20:29,437
Cast.

557
00:20:29,437 --> 00:20:32,481
♪

558
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:33,899
You're kidding me.

559
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:36,694
Diabolical, hardcore!

560
00:20:36,694 --> 00:20:38,446
(yelling)

561
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:41,115
♪

562
00:20:41,115 --> 00:20:41,907
Owned it!

563
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:42,992
Game over.

564
00:20:42,992 --> 00:20:45,244
Winner, Tetsuya Kurodake.

565
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:49,999
♪

566
00:20:49,999 --> 00:20:51,625
He actually did it!

567
00:20:51,625 --> 00:20:53,127
Incredible.

568
00:20:53,127 --> 00:20:56,255
Tetsuya just defeated the second
ranked fighter in grade sixth.

569
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,965
I don't believe it.

570
00:20:57,965 --> 00:20:59,049
Hey, Tetsuya.

571
00:20:59,049 --> 00:21:00,593
Not too bad out there.

572
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:02,428
It was all thanks to you, yo.

573
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:04,096
But you were playing the cards.

574
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,265
Unbelievable deck
building, man.

575
00:21:06,265 --> 00:21:08,392
There's no way I could do that.

576
00:21:08,392 --> 00:21:10,144
Sorry for what I said.

577
00:21:10,144 --> 00:21:12,605
Apology accepted, bro.

578
00:21:12,605 --> 00:21:14,231
How about Balle du Soleil?

579
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:15,566
Huh?

580
00:21:15,566 --> 00:21:17,693
It's French and it
means the Sun Rockets.

581
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:20,029
I was thinking it could
be our new team name.

582
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:21,238
So what do you say?

583
00:21:21,238 --> 00:21:23,491
You two have any
problems with that name?

584
00:21:23,491 --> 00:21:24,867
Nope, that works for me.

585
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:27,077
It sounds way better
than Sun Fighters.

586
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,913
Hey, doesn't my opinion count?

587
00:21:28,913 --> 00:21:31,081
And what about me, you guys?

588
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:34,418
Okay, we got our sights
set on the ABC Cup.

589
00:21:34,418 --> 00:21:37,588
Let's go, team Balle du Soleil.

590
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:38,923
Yeah!

591
00:21:46,806 --> 00:21:48,390
I just got unlucky.

592
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,936
I was careless because I
was fighting a total newbie.

593
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:54,522
Say that enough and
you might believe it.

594
00:21:54,522 --> 00:21:56,607
Huh?

595
00:21:56,607 --> 00:22:00,319
You're that old
guy from yesterday.

596
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:02,112
Okay, rub it in if you want.

597
00:22:02,112 --> 00:22:03,197
I don't care.

598
00:22:03,197 --> 00:22:04,532
Must have looked pretty funny

599
00:22:04,532 --> 00:22:06,116
seeing a second ranked fighter

600
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:09,119
defeated by a lowly
unranked challenger.

601
00:22:09,119 --> 00:22:11,580
Your ego's going to
hold you back, kid.

602
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:16,252
And what exactly makes you an
expert on the subject anyway?

603
00:22:16,252 --> 00:22:19,922
I'd like to offer you my
help, if you'll accept it.

604
00:22:19,922 --> 00:22:21,382
Just who are you, old man?

605
00:22:21,382 --> 00:22:24,218
And why are you following
me around everywhere?

606
00:22:24,218 --> 00:22:26,512
You can call me El Quixote.

607
00:22:26,512 --> 00:22:36,981
♪

608
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:41,819
A great Dragon Knight
here from Dragon World.

609
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,779
Dragon Knight

610
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:46,323
El Quixote.

611
00:22:49,994 --> 00:22:51,620
Hello there, I'm Paruko

612
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:54,164
here to guide you through
the world of Buddyfight.

613
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:55,791
Do you know about deck builders?

614
00:22:55,791 --> 00:22:57,668
They're our deck
designing specialists.

615
00:22:57,668 --> 00:22:59,003
Using their
extensive knowledge

616
00:22:59,003 --> 00:23:00,921
they analyze card
powers and abilities

617
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,799
to decide which cards should
go into the decks they create.

618
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:05,134
The strength and
usability of your deck

619
00:23:05,134 --> 00:23:06,552
can really vary a lot

620
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:08,888
depending on the skill
of your deck builder.

621
00:23:08,888 --> 00:23:10,431
It all sounds
pretty deep, I know.

622
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:11,724
Just remember
that it's important

623
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:14,727
to choose your
deck builder wisely.

624
00:23:14,727 --> 00:23:16,437
Can you open a Buddy rare card?

625
00:23:16,437 --> 00:23:18,439
What do you think?

626
00:24:49,029 --> 00:24:50,406
On the next Buddyfight,

627
00:24:50,406 --> 00:24:53,242
the final qualifier
of the ABC Cup begins

628
00:24:53,242 --> 00:24:55,536
and we'll see the top
ranked fighter of his grade,

629
00:24:55,536 --> 00:24:57,287
Zanya Kisaragi,

630
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:58,956
using the Katana World.

631
00:24:58,956 --> 00:25:01,208
Break past the final qualifier!

632
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:03,877
Keep on Buddyfighting.

